article.headline: Alcorn State 78, Grambling 77
article.story: GRAMBLING, La. (AP) -- Trey Johnson sank a jump shot at the buzzer to give Alcorn State a 78-77 win over Grambling State Monday night. Brian Jackson and John Chandler led five players in double figures for Alcorn State (7-13, 6-5 Southwestern Athletic Conference) with 18 points apiece. DeAndre Jones and Johnson added 12 each and Dion Callans had 10. Jones also pulled down eight rebounds for the Braves. Brion Rush led Grambling (7-14, 5-6) with 31 points and was 6-of-8 from 3-point range. Paul Haynes added 25 points and grabbed eight rebounds.
